
                                                              input-stream-p


    FUNCTION
    input-stream-p  -  test whether a stream is capable of input

    USAGE
    input-stream-p stream

    DESCRIPTION
    Returns true if STREAM, which must be a  stream,  is  capable  of  input
    operations, and false otherwise.

    EXAMPLES
    (input-stream-p *query-io*) => t
    (input-stream-p (make-string-output-stream)) => nil
    (input-stream-p *standard-input*) => t

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 21:332, output-stream-p, streamp













































